  "prompt": "How do I handle exam pressure?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to handle exam pressure:\n\n1. Preparation Strategies\n- Start studying early\n- Create a structured study schedule\n- Break study sessions into manageable chunks\n- Use active learning techniques\n- Practice past exam papers\n\n2. Mental Health\n- Get enough sleep\n- Practice deep breathing and relaxation techniques\n- Maintain a positive mindset\n- Use positive self-talk\n- Meditate or do yoga\n\n3. Physical Wellness\n- Eat healthy, balanced meals\n- Exercise regularly\n- Stay hydrated\n- Avoid excessive caffeine\n- Take short breaks during study sessions\n\n4. Stress Management\n- Identify and acknowledge your stress\n- Talk to friends or family\n- Consider counseling if feeling overwhelmed\n- Use stress-reduction apps\n- Listen to calming music\n\n5. Exam Day Preparation\n- Prepare materials the night before\n- Get a good night's sleep\n- Eat a nutritious breakfast\n- Arrive early at the exam venue\n- Take deep breaths before starting\n\n6. During the Exam\n- Read instructions carefully\n- Manage your time\n- Start with questions you're most confident about\n- Stay calm and focused\n\nRemember, everyone experiences exam pressure differently, so find strategies that work best for you.",
